article.headline: Texas-Arlington 83, North Texas 81
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Jermaine Griffin hit a jumper from the baseline as time expired Wednesday night to give Texas-Arlington an 83-81 victory over North Texas. Griffin led Texas-Arlington (2-0) with 24 points. He hit 8-of-13 from the field and 8-of-11 from the free throw line. He also had three blocked shots. All five of the Mavericks' starters scored in double figures. Rodrick Epps added 15 points and Ro'ger Guignard had 12. Anthony Vereen scored 11 and Larry Posey 10. Kendrick Davis scored 17 points and Keith Wooden added 16 to lead North Texas (2-1). Calvin Watson scored 12. Texas-Arlington led 39-38 at the half. The Mavericks shot 53 percent from the field to 47 percent for North Texas.
